    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="622"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.852/90: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-17T20:00:00-03:00"
                            >February 17, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:19 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>606. Department’s 530, February 16, 7 p.m.<note n="44" xml:id="d622fn44">Not
                        printed.</note> The Embassy and Brazilian Maritime Commission are in
                    agreement. Foreign Office is sending text to President Vargas for his approval.
                    The Embassy requests telegraphic authority to exchange notes with Foreign Office
                    based upon the text reported in the Embassy’s airgram 303 February 17, 2
                    p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
